https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/5eZqdfJDK9PZUIDPPSv7wZpG2JI.jpg Joined by the likes of saxophonist Ben Webster and trumpeter Cootie Williams, jazz giant Duke Ellington demonstrates in this collection of performance clips (spanning the years 1929-43) precisely why he's one of the seminal figures in American music. Ellington's musical evolution can be seen in excerpts from feature-length and short films that include Black and Tan, Check and Double Check, Symphony in Black and The Hit Parade of 1937. Duke Ellington & His Orchestra 1929-1943
